

---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Astro Learning Blog">
	<div slot="hero" class="space-y-4 rounded-xl bg-white/80 p-8 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-200">
		<p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-500">Module 1 · Foundations</p>
		<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Learning Astro by Building a Blog</h1>
		<p class="max-w-2xl text-lg text-slate-600">
			This project documents each step of my Astro journey: deliberate practice, thoughtful use of AI, and strong Git hygiene.
		</p>
	</div>

	<section class="space-y-4 rounded-xl bg-white/70 p-8 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-200">
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">What to Expect</h2>
		<p class="text-slate-600">
			The blog will grow module by module, covering layouts, content collections, routing, interactivity, testing, performance, and deployment.
			Each entry will summarize the goals, decisions, and lessons learned per module.
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-600">
			<li>Intentional pace focused on understanding both the “what” and the “why”.</li>
			<li>Hands-on practice using AI as a code reviewer and assistant, not an autopilot.</li>
			<li>Git discipline: feature branches → pull-request reviews → develop → main.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
